d1temp@dtek.chalmers.se (Michael Tempsch) writes:

>>My neighbor's cell-phone happens to broadcast some spurious signals, can 
>>I monitor those ?
>
>Yes you can. As long as you don't distribute what you hear 
>( tell anyone else what you've heard ) it's perfectly legal
>to listen to any signal that you can pick up on your reciever.
>
>DISCLAIMER: This is the situation in Sweden but I'd imagine the
>	    legal situation to be similar in most countries.
>
In the US it is illegal to monitor cellular calls. It is even illegal to 
sell scanners that can receive the cellular frequencies.

To my knowlegde it is forbidden in most countries. I know only two 
exceptions: Scandinavia and The Netherlands.

